Secondly, The Day of Grace ended with these Professors at that time when they committed some grievous Sin;
Cain's, when he killed his Brother; Ishmael's, when he mocked at Isaac, &c. and Esau when out of love to his Lusts, he despised, and sold his Birth-right. Beware, barren Professor; Thou mayst 〈◊〉
that in half a quarter of an hour, from the evil of which thou mayst not be delivered for ever and ever.

